The paper deals with properties of the MMSE function and its implications in Information Theory, specifically in the context of parallel degraded MIMO Gaussian channels. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves matrix analysis and linear algebra, which suggests the sub-categories cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.MM (Mathematical Methods), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible options. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the MMSE property to derive results in Information Theory, which could fall under the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
